entries.femaleVariant: I'll try.
You still wanna leave?
I'll try. Helps to keep it at the back of my mind.
You still think about leaving Night City?
How's life beyond Night City?
What do you do now?
So, how's life away from civilization?
So what do you do nowadays?
You ever recorded any cool braindances?
I want to see you.
Hey. That offer on the dam still on the table?
Course. This evening in the lakeshore cabin. You'll be there?
I'll try my best. See you then.
Changed my mind – let's go diving.
Had a change of heart. Wanna take a dive, after all.
Preem. Lakeshore cabin this evening. Don't keep me waiting.
What's new with the Mox?
How's virtu-tuning going? Scroll anything preem lately?
What's new with the Mox?
Changed my mind. I'll help with the Clouds.
I'll help you with Hiromi.
You know what... I've thought about it. I'll help you your Clouds situation.
I take back what I said. I'll help you take care of Hiromi.
[Hang up] See ya, Judy.
I take an interest in everything.
Why do you work in porn?
Let's change the subject.
Something else I wanted to talk about.
Guess I kinda have to be into a little bit of everything. When it comes to virtus, I'm mostly in it for the intel.
Always wondered – why the smut industry?
Maybe you should become their leader.
Why'd you join them in the first place?
Got another question.
Got another question on my mind.
Couldn't you replace Susie and lead the Mox?
How'd you hook up with the Mox in the first place?
[Lean] I'd like to spend more time with you.
If I wasn't always on the move, you and I could spend more time together, enjoy life...
[Step away] Let's talk a little while longer.
Let's talk a little while longer, before I have to delta somewhere.
You don't miss Night City?
Let's talk about something else.
You don't miss Night City at all?
Let's talk about something else.
I was just thinking of you. And before you ask – no, you weren't wearing clothes.
Hey, V.
What's new?
Oh, before I forget. Some lady called me – Elizabeth something. Said she had a job for someone with an eye for virtus.
Way ahead of ya.
What a mess of a job.
Just so happens I already took that job.
Ugh... What a dumpster fire of a case.
Heard there was some trouble in Japantown, at the parade.
That was me.
Don't know anything about it.
Yeeeahhh... That was kinda my fault.
Don't know anything about that.
Nothing special, same ol' story..
What else is going on, besides that?
How'd you get into braindances?
How'd you get into virtus, anyway?
Good to hear. I already lost hope in, well... pretty much everything.
It was an interesting case.
Thanks for thinking of me.
Nice of you to think of me, Judy.
As far as cases go, it was interesting.
What did you hear?
What did you hear?
Corpos opened fire, civilians were killed.
I'll call Maiko and set up the meet. You'll get specifics soon.
Told her to drop you a line.
Hey, don't mention it. I just hope she's worth the eddies.
No shit. And? How'd it pan out?
Hard for me to say at this stage.
Riiiight, "client confidentiality" and all that.
You manage to crack it?
In a manner of speaking.
Hope the same went for your comp.
Ha! Don't ask me how, but the second I heard, I knew you were involved!
Oh, y'know, same old. Rather hear what you've been up to.
I'd rather hear about you.
Susie isn't giving me the time of day – as usual.
Depends what you'd call "preem." Does smut count?
Got all the time in the world.
You mean seeing who killed who using what?
Something like that. But you see it differently – for you it's art.
Isn't it obvious? Two minutes of realfeel's a week's pay.
Sure, but I thought someone like you wouldn't be into the whole objectification thing.
Objectification? Not in my virtus. My actors love what they do, and that's why everyone wants to feel 'em. Can't fake old school emotions.
I always had a techie streak, ever since I was a little kid. When I felt my first virtu, I was like, "Hey, I can make this way better."
So I tried, and I did. And then it just snowballed from there.
Shoot.
I thought Susie and the gang could really change something in this city. I believed in them.
Wind up business as usual?
I mean, I wouldn't go that far. Few joytoys' lives've really changed for the better thanks to them.
Quality over quantity, V.
Just focus on tying up all your loose ends – then you and I are leaving this city once and for all.
Guarantee it does. People already say I've got a bounce in my step.
Yeah... someday.
But as of right now... I've still got a reason to stay.
Eh, it's too soon. I still remember the noise, the smell... everything.
Got for it. I'm driving right now, so it's perfect timing.
For you I've got all day.
You mean Night City? Ugh. You should see Oregon. This is how life's meant to be lived.
I'm taking things easy for now. But I'll get back to work soon. I've got an idea for an experimental virtu cycle.
Meet me early morning – H8 megatower, trashy terrace outside the upper level of Clouds. Just... be there this time.
V, just... Don't get cold feet this time.
Hahahaha. No way in hell. I'll stick with tuning virtus, thank you very much.
If you haven't noticed, I'm not much of a people-person.
We just wanted to talk to Hanako. Things went a little sideways from there.
Dealing with corps – what did you expect.
Huh, funny... Sounds like something you'd be in the know about.
It was nice catching up.
I'm right here, V – call me anytime.
You know anything about illegal braindances?
Had the pleasure of coming across some XBDs lately. You know much about them?
Lemme put it this way – the less I know about them, the better.
And I'm not even mentioning the producers.
I gotta go.
